Steps to enable Security

Step 1 : Add dependency

	- By default it will secure all endpoints with basic security(OOTB Spring security)
	
Step 2 : Create Configuration file 

	2A: Here we will be intercepting incoming http request and update SecurityFilterChain using HttpSecurity, to authorize and protect endpoints based on need
	
	2B : Creating password encoder bean - most commonly used password encoder is BCryptPasswordEncoder(Which will be helpful for User Registration)
	
	2C: Create user registration api
	


Step 3 : Enabling JWT (JSON Web Token)

	3A : Add jjwt dependencies in pom.xml
			like jjwt-api,jjwt-impl,jjwt-jackson from 
			
	3B : Create JwtUtil class
	
			- Responsible for Generating new token from username with expiration time
			
	3C : Create Login api
	
			- UserService will fetch user by unique value check if user exist
			-  check stored hash and incoming request has is equal if not throw exception 
			- if both hash equal from JwtUtil generate token